          <p>
            Argentina also signed new trade arrangements with the European Union, EFTA, and the United States, cut some export taxes, and sought membership in the OECD and CPTPP. International treaties matter because a future president will find them harder to reverse than Milei's own decrees.
          </p>
          <p>
            The October 2025 midterm elections gave Milei more support in Congress, though still not a majority of his own. Congress approved a proper 2026 budget and passed a broad labor reform, <a href="https://knowledge.dlapiper.com/dlapiperknowledge/globalemploymentlatestdevelopments/2026/argentinas-labor-modernization-bill-top-points" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Law 27,802</a>, in March 2026. It allows more flexible schedules and contracts, limits some severance payments and lawsuits, cuts some employment taxes, and creates employer-funded severance accounts. Future employment data will show whether it creates more registered jobs or mainly weakens worker protections. Because Congress passed a law, the next president cannot reverse it as easily as a decree.
          </p>
          <h3 id="what-milei-promised-but-has-not-delivered">What he has not delivered</h3>
          <p>
            Milei campaigned on <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/20/milei-wins-in-argentina-edging-the-country-closer-to-the-us-dollar.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">replacing the peso with the dollar</a>, closing the central bank, and privatizing pensions. None has happened. The peso and central bank remain, with the exchange rate allowed to move slowly inside an official range. Trust in the currency still depends heavily on this government keeping the budget balanced.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most currency controls have ended, but not all. Some old corporate debts, imports, and dividend payments remain controlled. Dollarization may have been impractical or unnecessary. But by dropping it, Milei also dropped the permanent barrier that was supposed to stop a future government from printing money again.
          </p>
          <p>
            The promised tax overhaul is also incomplete. Export taxes are lower but still exist. So do the tax on bank withdrawals, provincial taxes on business revenue, a 21% sales tax, and high employment charges. Argentina still has about 155 separate taxes, although just seven produce almost all revenue. About 44.1% of workers <a href="https://reason.org/commentary/tax-reform-is-essential-to-restore-prosperity-in-argentina/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">work off the books</a>. The government and IMF plan to simplify taxes gradually, but as of July 2026 most of that reform remains a plan.
          </p>
          <p>
            Privatization has also been slow. The Ley Bases allowed the full or partial sale of eight companies, but IMPSA was the first completed deal and major firms remain state-owned. Pension reform has been postponed. Under the <a href="https://www.imf.org/-/media/files/publications/cr/2026/english/1argea2026001.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">current IMF schedule</a>, the government will only begin designing it for a target at the end of 2027.
          </p>
          <h3 id="why-the-program-might-be-enough">Why it might be enough</h3>
          <p>
            Argentina does not need to fulfill every libertarian campaign promise to grow. It needs a believable ban on printing money to cover deficits, an exchange rate that does not make exports too expensive, simpler tax and labor rules, easier imports, and reliable property rights. Those changes would address most of the major failures described above.
          </p>
          <p>
            Investment in the Vaca Muerta oil and gas fields has already turned energy from a drain on dollar reserves into an export source. Mining and farming could broaden the country's exports further. The $28 billion in approved RIGI projects is stronger evidence than a business-confidence survey, although an approved project is not yet a working mine or factory. The IMF expects long-term growth near 3% a year. Because Argentina's population grows slowly, that rate would finally raise income per person above its post-2011 decline.
          </p>
          <h3 id="why-it-might-still-fail">Why it might still fail</h3>
          <p>
            The peso and the supply of dollars remain fragile. Argentina missed its 2025 target for usable dollar reserves. In early 2026, the IMF estimated that the central bank's true reserve position was about negative $10 billion after subtracting debts and borrowed reserves. The central bank then bought more than $10 billion by June, a major improvement. But currency swaps, IMF payments, and other dollar obligations mean the amount freely available is much lower than the total purchases suggest.
          </p>
          <p>
            The official exchange-rate range can again make the peso too expensive if Argentine prices rise faster than the peso falls. The IMF still says Argentina's ability to repay is <a href="https://www.imf.org/-/media/files/publications/cr/2026/english/1argea2026001.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">subject to exceptional risks</a>. Its forecast assumes Argentina can keep borrowing in markets, allow the exchange rate to adjust, and maintain political support for reforms.
          </p>
          <p>
            The balanced budget is real, but it is not yet protected by lasting institutions. Some early savings came from letting pensions and salaries fall behind inflation and nearly stopping infrastructure investment. Those sources cannot keep shrinking forever. An aging population, weak provincial finances, and the unreformed pension system will push spending upward.
          </p>
          <p>
            Cutting harmful taxes without reopening the deficit will require a more efficient state, a new agreement over national and provincial taxes, and broad economic growth. The 2026 labor law may make employers less afraid to hire, but it cannot by itself bring workers into the formal economy while employment taxes add 35–41% to labor costs. Weak schools, scarce domestic credit, and unpredictable courts also remain largely unchanged.
          </p>
          <p>
            Growth also remains concentrated in a few industries. Farming benefited from good weather. Energy benefited from exceptional geology and special investment guarantees. Part of the 2025 growth simply reversed the 2024 recession. RIGI's special promises exist precisely because ordinary Argentine rules are not yet trusted.
          </p>
          <p>
            A durable recovery requires small and medium businesses to invest without special deals. Argentina also needs more exports outside natural resources and far more private credit than today's roughly 15% of GDP. Without those changes, the country may become a more stable commodity exporter but still fail to approach the productivity and living standards of rich countries.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </main>

<script>
  const charts = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>("[data-gdp-chart]");
  const svgNamespace = "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg";
  const dimensions = {
    width: 760,
    height: 390,
    left: 88,
    right: 20,
    top: 48,
    bottom: 48
  };
  const plotWidth = dimensions.width - dimensions.left - dimensions.right;
  const plotHeight = dimensions.height - dimensions.top - dimensions.bottom;

  const formatValue = (value: number) =>
    new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", {
      style: "currency",
      currency: "USD",
      maximumFractionDigits: 0
    }).format(value);

  const xForYear = (year: number) =>
    dimensions.left + ((year - 1990) / 35) * plotWidth;
  const yForValue = (value: number, max: number) =>
    dimensions.top + plotHeight - (value / max) * plotHeight;

  charts.forEach((chart) => {
    const dataNode = chart.querySelector<HTMLScriptElement>("[data-gdp-data]");
    const svg = chart.querySelector<SVGSVGElement>("[data-chart-svg]");
    const hitArea = chart.querySelector<SVGRectElement>("[data-chart-hit-area]");
    const line = chart.querySelector<SVGPathElement>("[data-chart-line]");
    const area = chart.querySelector<SVGPathElement>("[data-chart-area]");
    const points = chart.querySelector<SVGGElement>("[data-chart-points]");
    const crosshair = chart.querySelector<SVGLineElement>("[data-chart-crosshair]");
    const selection = chart.querySelector<SVGCircleElement>("[data-chart-selection]");
    const yAxis = chart.querySelector<SVGGElement>("[data-y-axis]");
    const scrubber = chart.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>("[data-year-scrubber]");
    const yearOutput = chart.querySelector<HTMLOutputElement>("[data-year-output]");
    const readoutYear = chart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-readout-year]");
    const readoutValue = chart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-readout-value]");
    const readoutNote = chart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-readout-note]");
    const unit = chart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-chart-unit]");
    const estimateLegend = chart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-estimate-legend]");
    const buttons = chart.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-metric]");

    if (
      !dataNode || !svg || !hitArea || !line || !area || !points ||
      !crosshair || !selection || !yAxis || !scrubber || !yearOutput ||
      !readoutYear || !readoutValue || !readoutNote || !unit || !estimateLegend
    ) return;

    const series = JSON.parse(dataNode.textContent || "{}") as Record<
      "current" | "ppp",
      [number, number][]
    >;
    const config = {
      current: {
        max: 16000,
        ticks: [0, 4000, 8000, 12000, 16000],
        unit: "1990–2025 · current US$ at official period-average FX"
      },
      ppp: {
        max: 40000,
        ticks: [0, 10000, 20000, 30000, 40000],
        unit: "1990–2025 · current international dollars, PPP adjusted"
      }
    } as const;

    let metric: "current" | "ppp" = "current";
    let pinnedYear = 2025;

    const buildPath = (values: [number, number][], max: number) =>
      values.map(([year, value], index) =>
        `${index === 0 ? "M" : "L"} ${xForYear(year).toFixed(1)} ${yForValue(value, max).toFixed(1)}`
      ).join(" ");

    const renderSelection = (year: number) => {
      const point = series[metric].find(([pointYear]) => pointYear === year);
      if (!point) return;

      const [, value] = point;
      const x = xForYear(year);
      const y = yForValue(value, config[metric].max);
      crosshair.setAttribute("x1", String(x));
      crosshair.setAttribute("x2", String(x));
      selection.setAttribute("cx", String(x));
      selection.setAttribute("cy", String(y));
      scrubber.value = String(year);
      yearOutput.value = String(year);
      readoutYear.textContent = String(year);
      readoutValue.textContent = formatValue(value);

      const reconstructed = year >= 2007 && year <= 2015;
      const estimated = metric === "ppp" && year === 2025;
      readoutNote.textContent = estimated
        ? "Estimate · IMF extrapolation"
        : reconstructed
          ? "World Bank · post-2016 reconstruction"
          : "World Bank observation";
      svg.setAttribute(
        "aria-label",
        `${year}: ${formatValue(value)}, ${
          metric === "ppp" ? "PPP-adjusted international dollars" : "current US dollars"
        }. ${readoutNote.textContent}`
      );
    };

    const renderMetric = () => {
      const values = series[metric];
      const { max, ticks } = config[metric];
      const path = buildPath(values, max);
      line.setAttribute("d", path);
      area.setAttribute(
        "d",
        `${path} L ${xForYear(2025).toFixed(1)} ${(dimensions.top + plotHeight).toFixed(1)} L ${xForYear(1990).toFixed(1)} ${(dimensions.top + plotHeight).toFixed(1)} Z`
      );

      points.replaceChildren(...values.map(([year, value]) => {
        const point = document.createElementNS(svgNamespace, "circle");
        point.setAttribute("cx", String(xForYear(year)));
        point.setAttribute("cy", String(yForValue(value, max)));
        point.setAttribute("r", "2.2");
        return point;
      }));

      Array.from(yAxis.children).forEach((tickNode, index) => {
        const value = ticks[index];
        const y = yForValue(value, max);
        tickNode.querySelector("line")?.setAttribute("y1", String(y));
        tickNode.querySelector("line")?.setAttribute("y2", String(y));
        const label = tickNode.querySelector("text");
        if (label) {
          label.setAttribute("y", String(y + 4));
          label.textContent = value === 0 ? "$0" : `$${value / 1000}k`;
        }
      });

      buttons.forEach((button) =>
        button.setAttribute("aria-pressed", String(button.dataset.metric === metric))
      );
      unit.textContent = config[metric].unit;
      estimateLegend.hidden = metric !== "ppp";
      chart.dataset.activeMetric = metric;
      renderSelection(pinnedYear);
    };

    const yearFromPointer = (event: PointerEvent) => {
      const bounds = svg.getBoundingClientRect();
      const svgX = ((event.clientX - bounds.left) / bounds.width) * dimensions.width;
      return Math.min(2025, Math.max(1990, Math.round(
        1990 + ((svgX - dimensions.left) / plotWidth) * 35
      )));
    };

    buttons.forEach((button) => {
      button.addEventListener("click", () => {
        metric = button.dataset.metric === "ppp" ? "ppp" : "current";
        renderMetric();
      });
    });

    hitArea.addEventListener("pointermove", (event) =>
      renderSelection(yearFromPointer(event))
    );
    hitArea.addEventListener("pointerleave", () => renderSelection(pinnedYear));
    hitArea.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      pinnedYear = yearFromPointer(event);
      renderSelection(pinnedYear);
    });

    scrubber.addEventListener("input", () => {
      pinnedYear = Number(scrubber.value);
      renderSelection(pinnedYear);
    });

    svg.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
      if (!["ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight", "Home", "End"].includes(event.key)) return;
      event.preventDefault();
      if (event.key === "Home") pinnedYear = 1990;
      else if (event.key === "End") pinnedYear = 2025;
      else pinnedYear = Math.min(
        2025,
        Math.max(1990, pinnedYear + (event.key === "ArrowRight" ? 1 : -1))
      );
      renderSelection(pinnedYear);
    });

    renderMetric();
  });

  const incomeChart = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-income-chart]");
  if (incomeChart) {
    const dataNode = incomeChart.querySelector<HTMLScriptElement>("[data-income-data]");
    const svg = incomeChart.querySelector<SVGSVGElement>("[data-income-chart-svg]");
    const hitArea = incomeChart.querySelector<SVGRectElement>("[data-income-chart-hit-area]");
    const crosshair = incomeChart.querySelector<SVGLineElement>("[data-income-chart-crosshair]");
    const selection = incomeChart.querySelector<SVGCircleElement>("[data-income-chart-selection]");
    const scrubber = incomeChart.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>("[data-income-year-scrubber]");
    const yearOutput = incomeChart.querySelector<HTMLOutputElement>("[data-income-year-output]");
    const readoutYear = incomeChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-income-readout-year]");
    const readoutValue = incomeChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-income-readout-value]");

    if (
      dataNode && svg && hitArea && crosshair && selection && scrubber &&
      yearOutput && readoutYear && readoutValue
    ) {
      const values = JSON.parse(dataNode.textContent || "[]") as [number, number][];
      const startYear = 1990;
      const endYear = 2026;
      const max = 1400;
      let pinnedYear = endYear;

      const incomeXForYear = (year: number) =>
        dimensions.left + ((year - startYear) / (endYear - startYear)) * plotWidth;
      const incomeYForValue = (value: number) =>
        dimensions.top + plotHeight - (value / max) * plotHeight;

      const renderIncomeSelection = (year: number) => {
        const point = values.find(([pointYear]) => pointYear === year);
        if (!point) return;

        const [, value] = point;
        const x = incomeXForYear(year);
        crosshair.setAttribute("x1", String(x));
        crosshair.setAttribute("x2", String(x));
        selection.setAttribute("cx", String(x));
        selection.setAttribute("cy", String(incomeYForValue(value)));
        scrubber.value = String(year);
        yearOutput.value = String(year);
        readoutYear.textContent = String(year);
        readoutValue.textContent = formatValue(value);
        svg.setAttribute(
          "aria-label",
          `${year}: ${formatValue(value)} per month, median net income in constant 2026 US dollars.`
        );
      };

      const incomeYearFromPointer = (event: PointerEvent) => {
        const bounds = svg.getBoundingClientRect();
        const svgX = ((event.clientX - bounds.left) / bounds.width) * dimensions.width;
        return Math.min(endYear, Math.max(startYear, Math.round(
          startYear + ((svgX - dimensions.left) / plotWidth) * (endYear - startYear)
        )));
      };

      hitArea.addEventListener("pointermove", (event) =>
        renderIncomeSelection(incomeYearFromPointer(event))
      );
      hitArea.addEventListener("pointerleave", () => renderIncomeSelection(pinnedYear));
      hitArea.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
        pinnedYear = incomeYearFromPointer(event);
        renderIncomeSelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      scrubber.addEventListener("input", () => {
        pinnedYear = Number(scrubber.value);
        renderIncomeSelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      svg.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
        if (!["ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight", "Home", "End"].includes(event.key)) return;
        event.preventDefault();
        if (event.key === "Home") pinnedYear = startYear;
        else if (event.key === "End") pinnedYear = endYear;
        else pinnedYear = Math.min(
          endYear,
          Math.max(startYear, pinnedYear + (event.key === "ArrowRight" ? 1 : -1))
        );
        renderIncomeSelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      renderIncomeSelection(pinnedYear);
    }
  }

  const propertyChart = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-chart]");
  if (propertyChart) {
    const dataNode = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLScriptElement>("[data-property-data]");
    const svg = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGSVGElement>("[data-property-chart-svg]");
    const hitArea = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGRectElement>("[data-property-chart-hit-area]");
    const line = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGPathElement>("[data-property-line]");
    const points = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGGElement>("[data-property-points]");
    const crosshair = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGLineElement>("[data-property-chart-crosshair]");
    const selection = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGCircleElement>("[data-property-selection]");
    const yAxis = propertyChart.querySelector<SVGGElement>("[data-property-y-axis]");
    const scrubber = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>("[data-property-year-scrubber]");
    const yearOutput = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLOutputElement>("[data-property-year-output]");
    const readoutYear = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-readout-year]");
    const readoutValue = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-readout-value]");
    const readoutNote = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-readout-note]");
    const unit = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-unit]");
    const title = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-title]");
    const caption = propertyChart.querySelector<HTMLElement>("[data-property-caption]");
    const metricButtons =
      propertyChart.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-property-metric]");
    const basisButtons =
      propertyChart.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>("[data-property-basis]");

    if (
      dataNode && svg && hitArea && line && points && crosshair && selection &&
      yAxis && scrubber && yearOutput && readoutYear && readoutValue &&
      readoutNote && unit && title && caption
    ) {
      const data = JSON.parse(dataNode.textContent || "{}") as {
        prices: [number, number, number][];
        income: [number, number][];
      };
      const values = data.prices;
      const incomeByYear = new Map(data.income);
      const startYear = 1990;
      const endYear = 2026;
      const left = 88;
      const right = 20;
      const propertyPlotWidth = dimensions.width - left - right;
      const formatRent = (value: number) =>
        new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", {
          style: "currency",
          currency: "USD",
          minimumFractionDigits: 2,
          maximumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(value);
      const formatPercent = (value: number) =>
        `${new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", { maximumFractionDigits: 1 }).format(value)}%`;
      const formatYears = (value: number) =>
        `${new Intl.NumberFormat("en-US", { maximumFractionDigits: 1 }).format(value)} years`;
      const config = {
        "usd-buy": {
          min: 1250,
          max: 5000,
          ticks: [1250, 2500, 3750, 5000],
          getValue: (buy: number, _rent: number, _income: number) => buy,
          formatValue,
          formatTick: (value: number) => `$${value.toLocaleString("en-US")}`,
          title: "Buy and rent prices per square meter",
          unit: "1990–2026 · buy price in constant 2026 USD/m²",
          note: "Buy · per m²",
          caption: "Purchase prices per m², inflation-adjusted to 2026 dollars.",
          ariaUnit: "purchase price per square meter in constant 2026 US dollars"
        },
        "usd-rent": {
          min: 5,
          max: 20,
          ticks: [5, 10, 15, 20],
          getValue: (_buy: number, rent: number, _income: number) => rent,
          formatValue: formatRent,
          formatTick: (value: number) => `$${value}`,
          title: "Buy and rent prices per square meter",
          unit: "1990–2026 · monthly rent in constant 2026 USD/m²",
          note: "Rent · per m²/month",
          caption: "Monthly rent per m², inflation-adjusted to 2026 dollars.",
          ariaUnit: "monthly rent per square meter in constant 2026 US dollars"
        },
        "relative-buy": {
          min: 0,
          max: 60,
          ticks: [0, 20, 40, 60],
          getValue: (buy: number, _rent: number, income: number) =>
            (buy * 50) / (income * 12),
          formatValue: formatYears,
          formatTick: (value: number) => `${value}y`,
          title: "Years of median income needed to buy 50 m²",
          unit: "1990–2026 · 50 m² purchase ÷ annual median net income",
          note: "50 m² · years of income",
          caption: "Years of median net income needed to buy a 50 m² Recoleta property, assuming every dollar of income went toward the purchase.",
          ariaUnit: "years of median net income needed to buy a 50 square meter property"
        },
        "relative-rent": {
          min: 0,
          max: 210,
          ticks: [0, 70, 140, 210],
          getValue: (_buy: number, rent: number, income: number) =>
            (rent * 50 * 100) / income,
          formatValue: formatPercent,
          formatTick: (value: number) => `${value}%`,
          title: "Share of median income needed to rent 50 m²",
          unit: "1990–2026 · 50 m² monthly rent ÷ median monthly net income",
          note: "50 m² rent · share of income",
          caption: "Share of median monthly net income consumed by one month of renting 50 m² in Recoleta. 100% means the entire monthly income.",
          ariaUnit: "percent of median monthly net income needed to rent a 50 square meter property"
        }
      } as const;
      let metric: "buy" | "rent" = "buy";
      let basis: "usd" | "relative" = "usd";
      let pinnedYear = endYear;

      const propertyXForYear = (year: number) =>
        left + ((year - startYear) / (endYear - startYear)) * propertyPlotWidth;
      const propertyYForValue = (value: number, min: number, max: number) =>
        dimensions.top + plotHeight - ((value - min) / (max - min)) * plotHeight;
      type PropertyMode = keyof typeof config;
      const getConfig = () => config[`${basis}-${metric}` as PropertyMode];
      const getPropertyValue = (
        point: [number, number, number],
        modeConfig: (typeof config)[PropertyMode]
      ) => {
        const [year, buy, rent] = point;
        const income = incomeByYear.get(year);
        return income === undefined ? null : modeConfig.getValue(buy, rent, income);
      };

      const renderPropertySelection = (year: number) => {
        const point = values.find(([pointYear]) => pointYear === year);
        if (!point) return;

        const modeConfig = getConfig();
        const value = getPropertyValue(point, modeConfig);
        if (value === null) return;
        const x = propertyXForYear(year);
        crosshair.setAttribute("x1", String(x));
        crosshair.setAttribute("x2", String(x));
        selection.setAttribute("cx", String(x));
        selection.setAttribute(
          "cy",
          String(propertyYForValue(value, modeConfig.min, modeConfig.max))
        );
        scrubber.value = String(year);
        yearOutput.value = String(year);
        readoutYear.textContent = String(year);
        readoutValue.textContent = modeConfig.formatValue(value);
        readoutNote.textContent = modeConfig.note;
        svg.setAttribute(
          "aria-label",
          `${year}: ${modeConfig.formatValue(value)}, ${modeConfig.ariaUnit}.`
        );
      };

      const renderPropertyMetric = () => {
        const modeConfig = getConfig();
        const { min, max, ticks } = modeConfig;
        const metricValues = values.flatMap((point) => {
          const value = getPropertyValue(point, modeConfig);
          return value === null ? [] : [[point[0], value] as [number, number]];
        });
        const path = metricValues.map(([year, value], pointIndex) =>
          `${pointIndex === 0 ? "M" : "L"} ${propertyXForYear(year).toFixed(1)} ${propertyYForValue(value, min, max).toFixed(1)}`
        ).join(" ");
        line.setAttribute("d", path);

        points.replaceChildren(...metricValues.map(([year, value]) => {
          const point = document.createElementNS(svgNamespace, "circle");
          point.setAttribute("cx", String(propertyXForYear(year)));
          point.setAttribute("cy", String(propertyYForValue(value, min, max)));
          point.setAttribute("r", "2.2");
          return point;
        }));

        Array.from(yAxis.children).forEach((tickNode, index) => {
          const value = ticks[index];
          const y = propertyYForValue(value, min, max);
          tickNode.querySelector("line")?.setAttribute("y1", String(y));
          tickNode.querySelector("line")?.setAttribute("y2", String(y));
          const label = tickNode.querySelector("text");
          if (label) {
            label.setAttribute("y", String(y + 4));
            label.textContent = modeConfig.formatTick(value);
          }
        });

        metricButtons.forEach((button) =>
          button.setAttribute(
            "aria-pressed",
            String(button.dataset.propertyMetric === metric)
          )
        );
        basisButtons.forEach((button) =>
          button.setAttribute(
            "aria-pressed",
            String(button.dataset.propertyBasis === basis)
          )
        );
        title.textContent = modeConfig.title;
        unit.textContent = modeConfig.unit;
        caption.textContent = modeConfig.caption;
        propertyChart.dataset.activeMetric = metric;
        propertyChart.dataset.activeBasis = basis;
        renderPropertySelection(pinnedYear);
      };

      const propertyYearFromPointer = (event: PointerEvent) => {
        const bounds = svg.getBoundingClientRect();
        const svgX = ((event.clientX - bounds.left) / bounds.width) * dimensions.width;
        return Math.min(endYear, Math.max(startYear, Math.round(
          startYear + ((svgX - left) / propertyPlotWidth) * (endYear - startYear)
        )));
      };

      metricButtons.forEach((button) => {
        button.addEventListener("click", () => {
          metric = button.dataset.propertyMetric === "rent" ? "rent" : "buy";
          renderPropertyMetric();
        });
      });
      basisButtons.forEach((button) => {
        button.addEventListener("click", () => {
          basis = button.dataset.propertyBasis === "relative" ? "relative" : "usd";
          renderPropertyMetric();
        });
      });

      hitArea.addEventListener("pointermove", (event) =>
        renderPropertySelection(propertyYearFromPointer(event))
      );
      hitArea.addEventListener("pointerleave", () => renderPropertySelection(pinnedYear));
      hitArea.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
        pinnedYear = propertyYearFromPointer(event);
        renderPropertySelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      scrubber.addEventListener("input", () => {
        pinnedYear = Number(scrubber.value);
        renderPropertySelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      svg.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
        if (!["ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight", "Home", "End"].includes(event.key)) return;
        event.preventDefault();
        if (event.key === "Home") pinnedYear = startYear;
        else if (event.key === "End") pinnedYear = endYear;
        else pinnedYear = Math.min(
          endYear,
          Math.max(startYear, pinnedYear + (event.key === "ArrowRight" ? 1 : -1))
        );
        renderPropertySelection(pinnedYear);
      });

      renderPropertyMetric();
    }
  }
</script>

